              body: "Video creators obsess over the first three seconds. Text has the exact same gate: on LinkedIn, everything after roughly 200 characters hides behind 'see more'; on X and Threads, scroll speed means line one gets a half-second glance.\n\nSo structure your opening as a two-punch combination:\n\n- **Line 1 — the hook:** the boldest, most specific, most tension-loaded sentence in the entire post. Not a warm-up. Not context.\n- **Line 2 — the re-hook:** raises the stakes or sharpens the curiosity, converting the pause into the 'see more' tap.\n\nExample: 'We fired our best client last month.' / 'Revenue went up 30% within six weeks. Here's the math nobody runs.'\n\nThe cardinal sin is the **throat-clear** — openings like 'I've been thinking a lot lately about...' Delete the first sentence of your draft and the post almost always gets stronger. Professionals write the post first, then audition ten first lines against it."
