              body: "Before publishing one post, leave ten genuine comments on posts your target audience is already reading. This is the 10-before-1 rule, and it works through three simultaneous mechanisms:\n\n1. **Borrowed distribution.** Your comment sits under a post with established reach; every reader of that post can see your name, face, and headline. You are advertising on someone else's billboard, free.\n2. **Warmed networks.** People whose posts you thoughtfully engage tend to reciprocate — and on LinkedIn especially, early engagement on your own posts feeds the test-slice audition. Your commenting builds the exact audience whose golden-hour behavior decides your reach.\n3. **Algorithmic presence.** Active accounts appear in feeds more; ghost accounts that only broadcast get treated like ghosts.\n\nTime cost: 20-25 minutes daily. For accounts under 5,000 followers, those minutes routinely outperform an extra post. Commenting is not the warm-up act before the real work — early on, it *is* the real work."
