              body: "Each platform has a working cadence band — enough to stay in the feed's memory, not so much you cannibalize yourself:\n\n- **LinkedIn:** 3-5 posts/week. Posts live for days; stacking multiple in one day makes them compete in the audition stage. One per day is a ceiling.\n- **X:** 1-5 posts/day, plus reply activity. The timeline's short half-life makes higher volume necessary and safe.\n- **Threads:** 1-3 conversational posts/day. Low production cost keeps this sustainable.\n- **Facebook Page:** 3-4 posts/week; a Group needs 2-3 discussion prompts/week from you until members carry the culture.\n\nThe critical principle: **choose the floor you can sustain for six months, not the ceiling you can sprint for two weeks.** An account that posts 3x/week for a year beats one that posts daily for six weeks and vanishes — feeds reward recency and consistency, and audiences trust rhythm. Set your floor one notch below what feels ambitious. You can always raise a floor; recovering from a public burnout gap is harder."
