              body: "Sustainable output comes from batching, not daily inspiration. The professional content week separates modes:\n\n- **One writing block (90-120 min):** draft the whole week's posts in a single sitting. Momentum compounds — post four takes a third of the time post one took, because you're warm.\n- **One editing block (30-45 min, a different day):** cold-eyed revision. Run the ten-first-lines drill, tighten the ladders, sharpen the closing questions. Never edit in the same sitting you drafted; you can't see your own fresh text.\n- **Daily engagement blocks (20-25 min):** the 10-before-1 commenting routine plus golden-hour replies.\n\nPair the batch with a **pillar rotation** so you never face a blank page: for example Monday = point of view, Wednesday = story, Friday = tactical how-to. The rotation guarantees variety across your skill radar and turns 'what should I post?' — the question that kills consistency — into a fill-in-the-blank."
