              body: "The expert insight that changes everything: busy operators should never start from a blank page. Their expertise already exists — in sales calls, client meetings, decision memos, and rants over lunch. The job is **extraction**, not creation.\n\nThe core ritual is the **weekly extraction interview**: 30 minutes, recorded, run by whoever supports the content operation (a teammate, a ghostwriter, or the founder interviewing themselves into a voice-memo app). Questions that reliably strike ore:\n\n- 'What did a client get wrong this week — and what did it cost them?'\n- 'What decision did you make this week that most peers would have made differently?'\n- 'What question did you answer three times this month?'\n- 'What's a belief you held two years ago that you'd now argue against?'\n\nThirty minutes of recorded answers yields transcript material for five to eight posts. The founder spent half an hour talking — something they'd happily do anyway — and the engine handles everything downstream."
