              body: "On X, the highest-leverage distribution event is not the repost — it's the **quote tweet**. A repost passes your content along; a quote tweet *adds commentary*, which spawns fresh engagement on both posts and drags your original into new interest clusters.\n\nEngineering for quotes means writing posts that people can perform on top of:\n\n- **Strong claims with visible edges.** 'Cold outreach is dead for agencies under $50k/month' invites both 'exactly this' quotes and 'wrong, here's why' quotes — and both distribute you.\n- **Deliberately incomplete framings.** A confident take that omits one obvious consideration gets completed by quote-tweeters. This is a scalpel, not a club: the omission must be defensible, never ignorant.\n- **Lists people can rank or amend.** 'The 5 skills that matter for creators in 2026' begets quote tweets adding a sixth.\n\nThe risk ledger: takes with edges occasionally get ratioed. The expert calculus is that a defensible position argued civilly survives any ratio — but never manufacture outrage you don't believe. Audiences forgive wrongness; they never forgive fakeness."
